# Project Structure

- **Framework**: Next.js 15+ with the App Router and TypeScript (strict mode).
- **Blockchain Stack**: OnchainKit, wagmi v2, viem v2 targeting the Base network.
- **Styling**: TailwindCSS (dark mode by default) via [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) and [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs). Global styles in [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css).
- **App Shell**: Root layout at [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) and entry page at [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx).
- **Providers**: OnchainKit and app-wide providers are composed in [app/providers.tsx](mdc:app/providers.tsx) for Base network integration.
- **SVG Components**: Reusable SVGs live in [app/svg](mdc:app/svg/).
- **Config**: Next config at [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) (WalletConnect externals), TypeScript at [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) with path alias `@/*`.
- **Reference**: See [CLAUDE.md](mdc:CLAUDE.md) for a deeper overview.

## Environment Variables
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_ONCHAINKIT_API_KEY` (required by OnchainKit)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_ONCHAINKIT_PROJECT_NAME` (used in page metadata)

## Conventions
- Prefer server components by default; use client components only when needed (`"use client"`).
- Keep components small, composable, and colocate by feature within `app/`.
- Prefer absolute imports via `@/*` alias when appropriate; otherwise, keep relative paths tidy.
